+# VQA 6-Phase Re-pipeline (Qwen3-VL-8B teacher, RTX 4090) Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+>
+> **COMMITS:** The maintainer owns all commits ([[commits-are-user-owned]]). After each task's tests pass, **stage** changes and **stop for the maintainer to commit**. Suggested messages are given; do NOT run `git commit` / `git push`.
+
+**Goal:** Re-plan and run the VQA → LoRA → merge → swap → eval pipeline on a single **RTX 4090 (24 GB)**, using **Qwen3-VL-8B-Instruct** as the VQA teacher, sampling **six manipulation-phase frames** (approach, grasp, pick, move_to_plate, place, retract) per episode instead of 3 generic frames, while still covering the **7 question types** (Attribute / Mechanics / Reasoning / Spatial / Summary / Temporal / Trajectory) from `docs/project_report.html`.
+
+**Architecture:** Surgically extend `src/vlm_lora/gen_vqa_from_lerobot.py` with phase-based frame sampling and phase-aware QA templates, swap the teacher default to the 8B dense model (fits 24 GB; the 30B-A3B MoE does not), then run the *existing, unmodified* train/merge/swap/eval scripts. The VLM-LoRA flow is intentionally 4090-sized — only whole-VLA full-fine-tuning (which produced the `N1_7_fft_*` baselines) needs an H100. Finally, document the scripts in `docs/llm_vlm_finetuning_guide.html` and translate `docs/plans/*` to Traditional Chinese.
+
+**Tech Stack:** Python ≥3.10, `transformers` (Qwen3-VL, `AutoModelForImageTextToText` / `Qwen3VLForConditionalGeneration`), `peft`, `tyro`, `opencv`, `pytest`. Dataset: LeRobot v2 at `/home/asus/Gits/IsaacLab-GR00T/datasets`.
